ut one may be unprepared=\r\n (and ironically may not even want it!) when it comes in this life.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;As you\n do sadhana, try not to fancy too many specific&gt; desires. Nat=\r\nure has a delay mechanism in granting your desires (because of constraints =\r\non what Nature can give you right now, arising from YOUR&gt; OWN previous acti=\r\nons). So Nature sometimes gives you what you want LATE, when you no longer =\r\nwant it or want something else. For example, one may pray for great wealth =\r\none&#39;s whole life and be born as a rich but very sick man in next life. One =\r\nmay not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life for health. In the life after=\r\n that, one may be very healthy, but not have any knowledge or money. In ano=\r\nther &gt; case, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film. One may be rebo=\r\nrn &gt; as a tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not really enjoy tha=\r\nt &gt; experience. Basically, people keep going in circles through various liv=\r\nes, always &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, com=\r\ning back to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an out of body experience give=\r\nn by a\n rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from havin=\r\ng it in THIS life, one may be born in next life with this specific desire d=\r\nestined to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt;=\r\n &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0&gt; *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or =\r\npainful, if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to free it an=\r\nd it panicked so badly and started to shake violently. I went to save it fr=\r\nom a certain slow death and it was scared that I would kill it!&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; =\r\n&gt;&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this body-mind =\r\ncomplex and scared of being rescued from a certain slow death!&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;=\r\n&gt;If our ideas about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) are inc=\r\norrect and if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complete=\r\n realization of that at some stage involve stepping out of this body-mind\n =\r\ncomplex, without being scared?&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Kun=\r\ndalini rise after most undesirable conditioning is overcome, is far better =\r\nthan&gt; Kundalini rise forced when some really undesirable conditioning is st=\r\nill left in one&#39;s system.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;When one transcends one problematic =\r\nnotion about who one is and what one needs, another notion that lay buried =\r\ndeeper in consciousness may spring to the surface and torment one. If one o=\r\nvercomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another notion in one&#39;s b=\r\nody-mind complex that one&#39;s awareness clings on to (e.g. a great doctor, a =\r\ngreat leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). As an extreme example, i=\r\nf one person had a hidden deep desire to be a great soul who rescues the wo=\r\nrld, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y who will rescue the wor=\r\nld now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) deeply clings to any su=\r\nch notion, it can cause havoc. The person may show some\n signs of progress =\r\nand yet remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;An awakened K=\r\nundalini in a system with undesirable conditioning may accentuate one&#39;s wea=\r\nknesses and wrong notions heavily and cause serious psychiatric and spiritu=\r\nal problems.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=