 &g=\r\nt;&gt;Let me give an analogy. One wanting to move from\n one&#39;s small dilapid=\r\nated house (this&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; body-mind complex) to a huge palace (realized Sel=\r\nf) may first construct the palace over time and move into it when it is COM=\r\nPLETE. Alternately, if one occasionally goes and stays in the palace still =\r\nunder construction (analogy for out of body experiences due to Kundalini ri=\r\nse), is it an achievement? In fact, it comes with risks. The former approac=\r\nh is safer and one loses nothing in it. Similarly, one can progress towards=\r\n complete Self-realization without any out of body experiences. These are n=\r\not my word&#39;s, but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s words to Lord Rama.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt=\r\n;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Secondly, one does not get something without wanti=\r\nng it and putting sufficient effort towards it. One may have deeply desired=\r\n a Kundalini rise in a previous life and may have put enough effort. As a r=\r\nesult, one may be getting it now. But one may be unprepared (and ironically=\r\n may not even want it!) when it comes in this\n life.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp=\r\n;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;As you do sadhana, try not to fancy too many specific&lt;WB=\r\nR&gt;&gt; desires. Nature has a delay mechanism in granting your desires (beca=\r\nuse of constraints on what Nature can give you right now, arising from YOUR=\r\n&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; OWN previous actions). So Nature sometimes gives you what you wan=\r\nt LATE, when you no longer want it or want something else. For example, one=\r\n may pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and be born as a rich but very =\r\nsick man in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life fo=\r\nr health. In the life after that, one may be very healthy, but not have any=\r\n knowledge or money. In another &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; case, one may deeply desire to ac=\r\nt in a famous film. One may be reborn &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; as a tiger or a dog and act=\r\n in a famous film, but not really enjoy that &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; experience. Basicall=\r\ny, people keep going in circles through various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; som=\r\nething they are &quot;missing&quot;.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt;\n &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway=\r\n, coming back to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an out of body experience=\r\n given by a rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from h=\r\naving it in THIS life, one may be born in next life with this specific desi=\r\nre destined to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).&lt;WBR&gt;&g=\r\nt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt=\r\n;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painful=\r\n, if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt=\r\n;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I=\r\n went to free it and it panicked so badly and started to shake violently. I=\r\n went to save it from a certain slow death and it was scared that I would k=\r\nill it!&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;We are like that chipmunk,=\r\n glued to the mouse trap\n called this body-mind complex and scared of being=\r\n rescued from a certain slow death!&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&g=\r\nt;If our ideas about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) are in=\r\ncorrect and if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complet=\r\ne realization of that at some stage involve stepping out of this body-mind =\r\ncomplex, without being scared?&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise after m=\r\nost undesirable conditioning is overcome, is far better than&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; Kunda=\r\nlini rise forced when some really undesirable conditioning is still left in=\r\n one&#39;s system.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;When one transcends=\r\n one problematic notion about who one is and what one needs, another notion=\r\n that lay buried deeper in consciousness may spring to the surface and torm=\r\nent one. If one\n overcomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another=\r\n notion in one&#39;s body-mind complex that one&#39;s awareness clings on to (e.g. =\r\na great doctor, a great leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). As an =\r\nextreme example, if one person had a hidden deep desire to be a great soul =\r\nwho rescues the world, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y who w=\r\nill rescue the world now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) deepl=\r\ny clings to any such notion, it can cause havoc. The person may show some s=\r\nigns of progress and yet remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; =\r\n&gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;An awakened Kundalini in a system with unde=\r\nsirable conditioning may accentuate one&#39;s weaknesses and wrong notions heav=\r\nily and cause serious psychiatric and spiritual problems.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt=\r\n;&gt;The\n best approach I recommend is to NOT think in terms of Kundalini a=\r\nnd its rise. Just do sadhana, overcome your&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; weaknesses and improve=\r\n your detachment over time. Again, I want to emphasize that detachment is n=\r\not disgust or distaste for life/things/people around you. Disgust is the ot=\r\nher side of coin of attachment. It is a negative attachment.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&=\r\ngt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Don&#39;t worry about &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; wh=\r\nether your Kundalini rises or not. Worry about whether you are able to resi=\r\nst 6 internal enemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages (ashta pashas) or &lt;WBR&gt;&gt=\r\n; not. If your ability to resist them is increasing, you are making progres=\r\ns. EVEN IF your Kundalini is fast asleep, you are still making progress. Wh=\r\nen you completely overcome them, Kundalini (your self-awareness) &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; =\r\nwill automatically ascend to the top and meet Her Lord (true Self).&lt;WBR&gt;&gt=\r\n; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np;\n *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;W=\r\nBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;One word on surrendering to a personal deity. Though true s=\r\nurrender is helpful, most people do not have it. They simply do business wi=\r\nth god. Though people may be offended by my words, this is the plain and ba=\r\nre fact.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&quot;I want X, I will pray to=\r\n you and please give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am scared of Kundalini rise, I will pray=\r\n to you and please protect me&quot; - all this is just a business deal. There is=\r\n something you want and you ask god for it. True surrender has no place for=\r\n agendas, desires, demands or expectations. True surrender is losing onesel=\r\nf in one&#39;s fascination for the qualities of Lord. True surrender is accepti=\r\nng anything Lord throws one&#39;s way (whether it is pleasurable or highly pain=\r\nful) as Lord&#39;s prasad and accepting it gratefully. True surrender is thinki=\r\nng of Lord with fascination and pleasure, even in the face of (and\n during)=\r\n Death.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;If one without true surren=\r\nder and with many desires and wrong notions experiences a Kundalini rise, o=\r\nne may still be trapped, despite thinking of a personal god. It is not that=\r\n god does not want to &quot;protect&quot; one as said below. It is not about protecti=\r\nng or endangering. If you go back to my &quot;chipmunk glued to mouse trap&quot; exam=\r\nple above, I was trying to protect it, but it was scared. Similarly, one&#39;s =\r\nconditioning makes one *run away* from God&#39;s&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; protection! God&#39;s pro=\r\ntection may seem to a conditioned mind like grave danger that one should ru=\r\nn away from!&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;WBR&gt;&g=\r\nt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Whether through the path of wisdom or su=\r\nrrender, develop dispassion and detachment. Realize that all this is tempor=\r\nary and can be taken away anytime. Enjoy it while you have\n and keep doing =\r\nyour best, but be prepared to lose everything anytime. Only detachment and =\r\na very light mental conditioning (very light desires, dislikes etc) can pro=\r\ntect one as one&#39;s Kundalini rises to meet True Self. Heavy conditioning and=\r\n impurities in one&#39;s nadis will distract rising Kundalini (self-awareness) =\r\nand stop Her from meeting True Self.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&=\r\ngt;The real key is how light your conditioning is.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;=\r\nWBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Best regards,&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Narasimha&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n--------&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Astrology &amp; Spirituality Resources: &lt;A href=\r\n=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank&gt;http://=\r\nwww.vedicastrologer.org/&lt;/A&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;--------&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;WB=\r\nR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n&gt;________________________________&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; From: Leela Sast=\r\nry &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;To: &quot;&lt;A\n href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups=\r\n.co